Package common

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IChatRoom
    A generalized chat room interface that defines a set of operations of a chat room.
    ICmd2ModelAdapter<S,M extends IMessageType>
    This adapter is for the externally-sourced commands to interact with the local system
    IComponentFactory
    A factory for creating desired GUI components.
    ICRCmd2ModelAdapter
    This adapter is for the externally-sourced commands to interact with the local system, specifically the DataPacketCRAlgoCmd.
    ICRMessageType
    Chat-room-level message type that applies to all messages allowed in the chat-room-level communication
    IMessageType
    Top-level message type that restricts all message types allowed in the whole system.
    IReceiver
    IReceiver defines a receiver in a chat room, which corresponds to a user (More accurately, a remote user's chat room) in the remote.
    IUser
    IUser interface defines a set of operations of a user in our chatApp IUser is NOT transmitted to anyone.
    IUserCmd2ModelAdapter
    This adapter is for the externally-sourced commands to interact with the local system, specifically the DataPacketUserAlgoCmd.
    IUserMessageType
    User-level message type that applies to all messages allowed in the user-level communication
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DataPacketCR<T extends ICRMessageType>
    A more concrete data packet that holds a generic type of data, which will be used for transmitting messages in chat rooms.
    DataPacketCRAlgoCmd<T extends ICRMessageType>
    Specialized data packet processing command that uses DataPacketCR<T> and ICRCmd2ModelAdapters.
    DataPacketUser<T extends IUserMessageType>
    A more concrete data packet that holds a generic type of data, which will be used for transmitting messages between users.
    DataPacketUserAlgoCmd<T extends IUserMessageType>
    Specialized data packet processing command that uses DataPacketUser<T> and IUserCmd2ModelAdapter.
